cpp-httplib provides a header-only HTTP/HTTPS client and server library.

Usage:
    find_package(cpp-httplib CONFIG REQUIRED)
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE cpp-httplib)

For SSL support:
    find_package(cpp-httplib CONFIG REQUIRED COMPONENTS ssl)
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE cpp-httplib)

Example HTTP Server:
    #include <httplib.h>
    httplib::Server svr;
    svr.Get("/hi", [](const httplib::Request& req, httplib::Response& res) {
        res.set_content("Hello World!", "text/plain");
    });
    svr.listen("0.0.0.0", 8080);

Example HTTP Client:
    #include <httplib.h>
    httplib::Client cli("http://example.com");
    auto res = cli.Get("/");
    printf("%s\n", res->body.c_str());

For HTTPS/SSL server:
    #include <httplib.h>
    httplib::SSLServer svr("/path/to/cert.pem", "/path/to/key.pem");
    svr.listen("0.0.0.0", 443);

Install with SSL:
    vcpkg install cpp-httplib[ssl]
